## POST New Rule

```sh
/rules
```
Post Specific day body example:
{
    "specificDay": 
    {
        "day": "04-01-2018",
        "intervals": [
            {
                "start": "14:30", "end": "15:00" 
            }, { 
                "start": "15:10", "end": "15:30" 
            }
        ]
    }
}
Sample response:
{
    "intervals": [
        {
            "start": "14:30",
            "end": "15:00"
        },
        {
            "start": "15:10",
            "end": "15:30"
        }
    ],
    "type": "specificDay",
    "day": "04-01-2018",
    "id": 3
}

Post daily rule body example:
{
    "daily": 
        {
            "intervals": [
                {
                    "start": "5:00", "end": "15:00" 
                }
            ]
        }
}
Sample response:
{
    "intervals": [
        {
            "start": "5:00",
            "end": "15:00"
        }
    ],
    "type": "daily",
    "id": 4
}

Post weekly rule body example: 
//0..6 where 0 is sunday and 6 is saturday
{
    "weekly": 
    {
        "dayOfWeek": 1,
        "intervals": [
            {
                "start": "14:30", "end": "15:00" 
            }, { 
                "start": "15:10", "end": "15:30" 
            }
        ]
    }
}
Sample response:
{
    "intervals": [
        {
            "start": "14:30",
            "end": "15:00"
        },
        {
            "start": "15:10",
            "end": "15:30"
        }
    ],
    "type": "weekly",
    "dayOfWeek": 1,
    "id": 5
}


## GET All Rules

```sh
/rules
```
Sample response:
[
    {
        "intervals": [
            {
                "start": "5:00",
                "end": "15:00"
            }
        ],
        "type": "daily",
        "id": 0
    },
    {
        "intervals": [
            {
                "start": "14:30",
                "end": "15:00"
            },
            {
                "start": "15:10",
                "end": "15:30"
            }
        ],
        "type": "specificDay",
        "day": "04-01-2018",
        "id": 1
    }
]

## DELETE Rule

```sh
/rules/:id
```
Request example:
/rules/1
This request will respond the remaining rules

## GET Working Hours

```sh
/workinghours/:startDate/:endDate
```
Request example:
/workinghours/01-01-2018/04-01-2018
Sample response:
[
    {
        "day": "01-01-2018",
        "intervals": [
            {
                "start": "5:00",
                "end": "15:00"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "day": "02-01-2018",
        "intervals": [
            {
                "start": "5:00",
                "end": "15:00"
            },
            {
                "start": "5:00",
                "end": "15:00"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "day": "03-01-2018",
        "intervals": [
            {
                "start": "5:00",
                "end": "15:00"
            },
            {
                "start": "5:00",
                "end": "15:00"
            }
        ]
    }
]
